On Oct 20, 2007, at 12:19 PM, Rob wrote:

> I was reading last night and it looks like there is a "right" and a  
> "left" heads, is that just because of the temp sender or does it  
> 'really' matter?

Is the fuel mixture affected if you use the left head on the right? I  
don't know...

> Are there 'bad' push rod tube seals out there?

Yes, Viton seals are preferred.

> Is there a specific problem on the heads that I can look for that  
> would be a show stopper for me without machining or replacing the  
> head?

Cracks. They can be hard to see so clean up the head, get out a  
magnifier and start with the ports.

